../../planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-02.md:20:This is the strongest step in the chain because it demands scope control early. But it hides the hardest issue inside the word "admits." For observables like cumulative positive strain or deformation growth, admissibility is not a light bookkeeping matter. On the suitable weak / LEI floor, there is no honest Lagrangian flow map with the regularity needed to define many deformation-based quantities in the way the rest of the chain seems to want. If the branch already expects this, then Step 1 is mostly a kill switch, not a route-building step.
