../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:1:# Chain 04 - Adapted-Package Geometric Vorticity Route From Local Beltrami Deficit To Criterion Scale
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:5:The old neutral-Eulerian geometry package is already weak, so geometry is live only if the package change is stated openly and audited honestly. This chain asks whether one adapted localization package can turn local Beltrami deficit, direction coherence, or tube persistence into a theorem-facing geometric criterion or full-stretching reduction without hiding the gain inside the package itself.
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:13:### Step 1 - Declare the package change and fix the comparator
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:17:- Action: name the killed neutral-Eulerian package as the mandatory comparator.
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:18:- Action: state what exact burden the package change is supposed to improve: persistence, criterion compatibility, or full-stretching control.
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:19:- Expected output: a package-change memo with one comparator and one claimed advantage.
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:22:### Step 2 - Freeze one geometric observable family and one criterion endpoint
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:25:- Action: choose one promoted observable family only: local Beltrami deficit, direction coherence, Beltrami-plus-concentration, or direction-coherence-plus-persistence.
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:26:- Action: choose one endpoint family, preferably a Constantin-Fefferman-type geometric criterion or one fixed full-stretching target.
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:40:### Step 4 - Test the promoted observable on the full stretching mechanism
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:43:- Action: freeze one stretching representation and test whether the observable acts on the full mechanism rather than only on local Lamb-vector depletion or a descriptive fragment.
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:45:- Expected output: one stretching-control memo.
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:46:- Kill condition: if the observable controls only local depletion while the full stretching burden remains free, stop and write a full-stretching obstruction.
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:48:### Step 5 - Bridge to criterion scale or contradiction scale
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:51:- Action: write one explicit criterion-scale proposition or contradiction line using the promoted observable and the chosen package.
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:52:- Action: compare it against the neutral-Eulerian benchmark and the closest Constantin-Fefferman-type prior art.
../../planning-runs/run-009/planner-chains/chain-04.md:60:- Action: if negative, classify failure as package theater, persistence collapse, hidden derivative debt, full-stretching failure, or prior-art collapse.
