../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:19:- The proposed target quantities are also too easy to game. "Critical-norm transfer" or "stretching-facing spectral production" can be named without any prior reason to think they survive localization, time integration, or cancellation.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:53:- The expected output asks whether the mechanism can become a usable estimate, conditional criterion, or scenario exclusion. Those are very different deliverables. Lumping them together hides the fact that the route from triad geometry to each one has different failure modes.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:63:- The negative-output option is safer, but it may end up too weak to matter: "these audited helical candidates do not yield a usable lever for this audited target quantity and triad class." That is honest, but it is narrower than the chain's central premise and may have limited mission value unless calibrated against strong prior art.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:70:The chain treats "exact NS triad geometry differs from Tao-averaged geometry" as though this is already close to a breakthrough criterion. It is not. The missing ingredient is a mechanism that survives summation, localization, and dynamics. The chain acknowledges this only late.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:92:The central premise already assumes that the missing discriminator "may" live at the helical or triad level. That may be true, but the chain does not build in a strong competing hypothesis that the exact triad geometry is real yet irrelevant. As written, it leans toward trying to rescue a triad mechanism instead of aggressively testing whether triad structure is just a descriptive shadow of deeper geometric dynamics.
