../../planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-02.md:11:- The choice set is too broad. "Helical decomposition," "triad-symbol coefficients," shell flux, enstrophy production, stretching transfer, sign, cancellation, coercive depletion, and derivative-count improvement are not comparable objects. A branch can survive by picking the easiest symbolic package and the softest notion of gain.
../../planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-02.md:18:## Step 2 - Build the exact triad ledger and the Tao comparator
../../planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-02.md:22:- The "Tao comparator" is not fixed tightly enough. Which averaged model, preserving which invariants, at which comparison granularity? Without that, "Tao-sensitive" can become a rhetorical label instead of a mathematically checkable distinction.
../../planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-02.md:34:- Restricting to one promoted mechanism is good discipline, but it happens too late. The prior-art benchmark should come before promotion, not after. Otherwise the chain can spend time promoting a mechanism that is just a repackaging of Waleffe-type helical interaction lore, Beltrami depletion rhetoric, or decimated-shell intuition.
../../planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-02.md:45:- "Restore the full triad sum" is the real proof problem, but the chain gives no criterion for what would count as surviving it. Without an explicit summability target, a favorable-sign subset can look encouraging even when it is drowned by the rest of the ledger.
../../planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-02.md:67:- The route is highly exposed to prior-art overlap. Helical-sign classes, Beltrami depletion, restricted interaction geometry, and shell-transfer rhetoric have been mined for years. The chain recognizes this, but too late. The literature filter should be front-loaded, not attached after mechanism promotion.
