../../planning-runs/run-006/selector.md:23:- The set avoids redundancy better than any portfolio containing `chain-04`, because `chain-04` also tries to reach stretching control but does so through a heavier package-change burden.
../../planning-runs/run-006/selector.md:29:- It is less cleanly differentiated in target than `chain-03` because it still aims at stretching or criterion control, but with additional persistence, matching, and normalization debt.
../../planning-runs/run-006/selector.md:31:- Relative to `chain-03`, it contributes less portfolio breadth. Relative to `chain-01`, it is the less direct route to pressure/stretching relevance.
