../../planning-runs/run-006/planner.md:16:Central premise: the exact tensor coupling among `S`, `omega`, and `nabla^2 p` may contain a coercive or cancellation mechanism that scalar norm methods erase, especially at the full-stretching level or in the harmonic moments that survived the old far-field audit.
../../planning-runs/run-006/planner.md:28:Central premise: the only admissible Lorentz/weak-type route is one that replaces the exhausted strong-type De Giorgi mechanism rather than tuning it. The question is whether weak-type structure supports a genuinely different endpoint criterion or concentration architecture.
../../planning-runs/run-006/planner.md:36:Why it belongs now: the prior geometry branch left one informative survivor, `direction coherence + tube persistence`, but it died on the neutral package rather than under every possible geometric packaging.
../../planning-runs/run-006/planner.md:40:- Chain 01 is tensorial and local-to-nonlocal. It targets full stretching and pressure-Hessian structure directly.
../../planning-runs/run-006/planner.md:42:- Chain 03 is endpoint-functional rather than structural in the geometric sense. It audits weak-type architecture while forbidding a return to the dead strong-type iteration.
../../planning-runs/run-006/planner.md:43:- Chain 04 is geometric and transport-facing. It is the only chain that explicitly changes localization package and treats that change as part of the audited burden.
../../planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:13:This critique lands. The mission context already fixes several baseline facts: scalar truncation survives in SQG but not NS, the vorticity route still hits the same `beta = 4/3` wall, and Beltrami cancellation is fragile. A comparison matrix is only useful if it is explicitly organized around the operative localized or truncated term that needs improvement. As written, Step 1 could generate a clean survey without narrowing the live candidate set.
../../planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:35:### 3. Step 3 is partly mis-aimed because it uses Beltrami tests as if they were positive evidence
../../planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:39:The critique is right that exact Beltrami flows are too nongeneric to serve as positive confirmation of a generic NS mechanism, and the mission context already records that the cancellation is not robust under very small perturbation. It is also correct that an undefined notion of "small perturbation away from Beltrami alignment" is too loose.
../../planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:41:But the attack goes too far if it implies Step 3 should not do robustness testing at all. Robustness testing is exactly what should happen once a candidate has shown an estimate-level improvement. The correction is to demote Beltrami from a positive benchmark to a fragility screen:
../../planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:43:- if the candidate only works in exact or near-exact Beltrami regimes, it should be handed off to the geometry branch and counted as an algebraic failure here;
../../planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:77:- Beltrami fragility is already known.
../../planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:78:- If the branch becomes primarily about alignment geometry, it has drifted into Chain 03 territory.
../../planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:86:This lands across the board. Early kill conditions are too permissive because they allow formal or identity-level survival. The later kill condition around Beltrami fragility is closer to the right standard, but by then the branch may already have spent budget on dead candidates. The refined chain should instead kill candidates as soon as they fail either of these two gates:
../../planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:89:- or the only surviving signal is a geometry-only near-Beltrami effect.
../../planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:109:- and treat Beltrami/alignment behavior only as a fragility screen and branch-handoff condition.
../../planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:120:- There is a much smaller chance of a positive structural hit. A genuinely new algebraic cancellation that is estimate-level relevant, survives the Tao screen, and is not just near-Beltrami geometry remains unlikely.
