../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:27:### 3. The branch is too biased toward algebraic rewrite-hunting and sidelines dynamic or geometric structure
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:47:This concern is real but not fatal. The project already knows that the vorticity route hits the same `beta = 4/3` barrier and that Beltrami cancellation is fragile. Retesting those directions is only justified if the refined chain states exactly what new localized estimate, commutator accounting, or Tao-relevant comparison is being added.
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:75:This is a fair criticism. Given what is already known about Beltrami fragility, geometry should be part of the first serious evaluation, not a late purity test. The refined chain should specify the perturbation metric early and classify candidate signals as generic, geometry-entangled, or geometry-only.
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:77:The attacker is also right that algebraic and geometric structure need not separate cleanly. So the handoff rule has to be more careful: only pure geometry-only survival should close this branch outright.
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:7:The strongest version of the critique is not "this is obviously false." It is: the chain has not yet shown that there exists even one concrete reformulated unknown for 3D NS whose exact equation is structurally closer to SQG than to an LEI/CZ repackaging. Until that existence question is tightened up, the chain risks spending budget on elegant repackaging rather than on a genuinely Tao-sensitive mechanism.
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:16:- The step forbids "prettier notation" rewrites of the LEI flux, but that filter is too weak. A reformulation can avoid looking like the old LEI while still being mathematically equivalent to the same quadratic bookkeeping after one inverse operator or one projection. The real exclusion test should be stronger: does the new variable produce an exact equation whose leading bad term is not merely the old nonlinearity conjugated by a singular integral?
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:17:- The endpoint choices are too coarse. "Localized regularity," "continuation criterion," and "concentration exclusion" have very different burdens. A commutator that helps in a continuation criterion may be useless for localization once cutoff commutators and pressure recovery are inserted. Freezing only the endpoint family does not prevent later goalpost shifting.
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:27:- The chain says "promote one commutator candidate," but gives no criterion for dominance. In SQG, the commutator is not cosmetically present; it is the mechanism that actually controls the drift contribution. For NS, many candidate commutators will exist formally, but unless one quantitatively absorbs or re-expresses the dangerous term, the commutator is just a decorative byproduct of rewriting.
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:50:- The phrase "benchmarked gain" is vague. Benchmarked against what? The De Giorgi 4/3 wall? A Serrin-type criterion? A CKN concentration measure? Without a frozen baseline scale and norm, Step 4 can overcount marginal algebraic improvements that do not move any theorem-facing threshold.
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:59:- The criterion "narrower than arbitrary finite-energy regularity" is too weak. Many useless lemmas are narrower than full regularity while still being effectively equivalent to the hard case. For example, "control one compensated scalar with enough regularity to reconstruct all bad NS terms" is formally narrower but substantively the same problem.
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:74:The route is reformulation-first. That is both its novelty and its risk. Reformulation-heavy branches often generate exact equations with impressive-looking commutators and extension variables, only to discover that the nonlocal quadratic burden has merely moved. The chain does not contain a hard enough anti-repackaging criterion early enough in the process.
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:86:The chain says it is theorem-facing, but it does not freeze a baseline criterion, norm, or quantitative threshold at the start. Because of that, "one benchmarked gain" can end up meaning only that some reformulated term looks better than before, not that any known barrier has been moved in a theorem-relevant way.
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:102:- Freeze one explicit baseline criterion and one gain type at the start.
