../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-03.md:15:This is reasonable as a scoping move, but it hides the central failure mode. The space of choices is too broad relative to the proof burden. "Stochastic Kelvin circulation," "stochastic Cauchy formula," "backward stochastic flow," and "a martingale adapted to vorticity/stretching" are not comparable objects. They live at different regularity levels, encode different information, and have different endpoint plausibility. Putting them in one menu risks wasting effort on representational variety rather than selecting the one object most likely to interact with a blowup mechanism.
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-03.md:17:The endpoint menu is also under-argued. "Continuation criterion," "local concentration exclusion," and "contradiction line for blowup concentration" are not equally reachable. A continuation criterion usually demands a norm or structural quantity with clear coercive content. Local concentration exclusion is more local and may fit stochastic transport better. A contradiction line for blowup concentration is the vaguest of the three and can absorb failure without producing real progress. As written, the step lets the researcher pick the endpoint after the fact, which biases the chain toward survivable narrative rather than the hardest honest target.
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-03.md:25:The phrase "separate exact stochastic structure from merely formal probabilistic packaging" is good, but the chain does not specify a test strong enough to do that separation. Exactness alone is not the right discriminator. Many exact stochastic representations are just nonlinear Duhamel formulas in probabilistic clothing. The real test is whether the formula exposes a quantity that is better aligned with singularity prevention than the deterministic formulations already are. That criterion should be explicit here.
../../planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-03.md:39:This is where the real work should happen, and the chain has not prepared enough for it. By this point it still has not required identification of a concrete coercive observable, only an "exact stochastic identity" and a Tao-comparator memo. That makes Step 4 do all the heavy lifting at once: convert a representation into an actual estimate, absorb stopping/localization debt, and connect to a singularity endpoint. In practice, this is where most such routes collapse.
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:5:The attacker is substantially right that the original chain is disciplined but procedurally biased toward an early negative verdict. The original chain's core strength should be preserved: any geometry-first route must eventually control the full stretching mechanism and not just a visually local fragment. But several parts of the chain need tightening before a negative verdict would be trustworthy.
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:13:The attack is right that the Tao/NS-specificity filter is not operational enough as written. "Identify the exact ingredient" is still too impressionistic unless each candidate ingredient is translated into a concrete benchmark against averaged-model robustness and against known geometric regularity mechanisms. The critique is also right that transport laws, algebraic identities, and multiscale coherence mechanisms should not be mixed without separate tests.
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:25:The attacker is right that "Beltrami deficit," "vorticity-direction regularity," and "tube persistence" are not cleanly disjoint until localization scales, amplitude thresholds, and scenario classes are fixed. The refined chain should define observables jointly with the localization protocol rather than pretending they are independent primitives.
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:33:### 5. Step 2 is too anchored to known criteria and to "Beltrami deficit alone"
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:37:This is a real weakness. The original chain would too quickly conclude failure if Beltrami deficit alone does not imply an existing criterion. A viable route may require a hybrid observable, for example Beltrami deficit plus concentration, anisotropy, or tube-family coherence. The refined chain should allow that.
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:49:The attacker is correct. `u x omega` is not the stretching term. Its appearance in the Step 3 kill condition weakens confidence that the target mechanism has been fixed sharply enough. The refined chain should remove that language and focus only on representations of `S omega . omega`.
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:79:The chain is intentionally obstruction-first, and that is not itself a flaw. But the accumulation of early kill conditions, undefined terms, and decomposition freedom does create a procedural bias toward a polished negative memo. The refined chain should keep the obstruction discipline while delaying terminal judgments until the observables, scenario, and stretching representation are fixed.
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:85:This is a real issue. Because the chain sits directly in an area with substantial prior work, it needs explicit calibration against Constantin-Fefferman-Majda, later vorticity-direction coherence work, and related geometric depletion or near-Beltrami discussions before claiming novelty or NS-specificity.
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:91:- the chain must test control of the full stretching mechanism rather than a local geometric proxy alone;
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:100:- calibrate against prior art before invoking novelty or Tao-blocking;
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:103:- fix a kernel-level stretching representation before speaking of a nonlocal remainder;
../../planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:112:Rationale: the chance of a true breakthrough to a new regularity mechanism remains modest, but the refined protocol has a good chance of producing something mission-worthy: either a calibrated obstruction taxonomy, a sharp negative result about a specific geometric observable, or a narrowed hybrid observable worth carrying forward.
