../../planning-runs/run-005/selector.md:18:Chain 03 stays in because it preserves the strongest pressure-adjacent live lead without sliding back into the dead coefficient-shrinkage architecture. It is materially different from Chain 02: the unit of attack is not Fourier triads but the full stretching mechanism `S omega . omega` together with pressure-Hessian debt. It is also likely to produce a calibrated obstruction even if it does not promote to proposition scale, which makes it a strong third slot.
../../planning-runs/run-005/selector.md:22:Chain 04 is the best surviving geometry reboot, but it is the weakest of the four on expected value. Its first likely breaks are transport persistence, localization debt, and outside-region strain freedom, which means it is more exposed to dying before it reaches a criterion-scale statement. It is genuinely different, but the selected set already achieves strong diversity across global compactness, exact symbolic algebra, and tensorial stretching analysis while keeping a better balance of upside and useful failure output.
../../planning-runs/run-005/selector.md:36:Best pressure-adjacent route still alive after earlier eliminations. It engages the central stretching bottleneck directly and should still return a useful non-coercivity diagnosis if it fails.
