../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:60:- Action: state whether the observable will live directly on the theorem floor or on one proxy class, and if proxy-based, write the exact bridge burden back to suitable-weak / LEI data.
../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:61:- Action: name the closest live geometric prior art as the primary comparator and keep the killed neutral-Eulerian package only as a secondary comparator.
../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:63:- Expected output: an endpoint-and-comparator memo containing one candidate theorem-facing statement and one admissibility claim.
../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:95:### Step 5 - Audit contact with full stretching in a representation-robust way
../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:98:- Action: test the promoted observable against a canonical stretching representation and check that the conclusion survives translation to any alternate representation used for the claim.
../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:100:- Action: require either a quantitatively meaningful burden share of the full stretching term or a precise explanation of how the controlled share propagates to the endpoint.
../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:101:- Expected output: a full-stretching audit with unpaid remainder clearly identified.
../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:102:- Kill condition: if the observable controls only a local depletion fragment, only works in one friendly representation, or never changes the inherited endpoint ledger, stop with a full-stretching obstruction.
../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:112:- Action: benchmark the artifact against the closest live geometric prior art and the neutral-Eulerian comparator.
../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:114:- Kill condition: if the artifact merely repackages direction coherence, Beltrami depletion, or tube persistence without a stronger insertion point than prior art, stop with a prior-art absorption obstruction.
../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:126:- Action: state exactly which endpoint, admissibility standard, comparator, package, observable, burden currency, and stress tests were audited.
../../planning-runs/run-010/winning-chain.md:135:The likely presentable result is still a disciplined obstruction memo rather than a positive geometric mechanism. That is acceptable because this chain is explicitly designed to test whether geometry buys a theorem-facing lever after theorem-floor admissibility, same-currency budgeting, and full debt charging, not to rescue geometry by packaging alone.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:5:This chain is more disciplined than a naive geometry reboot, but it is still structurally tilted toward rescuing a preferred geometric story rather than proving that geometry actually buys a new theorem-facing lever. Its main weakness is that Steps 1 through 4 are mostly packaging, screening, and accounting moves; the first hard theorem-facing burden is postponed until Step 5. That makes it too easy for the chain to survive on increasingly careful descriptions of localization debt without ever producing a gain that is meaningfully stronger than existing geometric depletion or direction-coherence heuristics.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:11:### Step 1 - Declare one package change, one comparator, and one claimed advantage
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:15:The comparator is also too weak. Naming the `killed neutral-Eulerian package` is useful for local bookkeeping, but beating an already rejected package is not evidence of theorem relevance. The real comparator should be the closest live geometric prior art, especially Constantin-Fefferman style direction-control frameworks. Otherwise the chain can report progress while only outperforming a strawman that the portfolio has already discarded.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:17:The claimed advantages are too heterogeneous: `persistence`, `criterion compatibility`, and `control of the full stretching mechanism` are not nearby goals. Persistence is a packaging property; criterion compatibility is an endpoint-interface property; full stretching control is a mechanism claim. Letting Step 1 choose among those means the chain can quietly lower the bar before any serious work starts.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:21:### Step 2 - Freeze one geometric observable family, one scenario class, and one endpoint
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:25:There is also a hidden mismatch problem. `Local Beltrami deficit`, `direction coherence`, and `Beltrami-plus-concentration` are not interchangeable currencies, and neither are `Constantin-Fefferman-type criterion` and `one fixed full-stretching target`. Some pairings are much more natural than others. The step never requires the chain to justify why the chosen observable is even in the right currency for the chosen endpoint. It only requires a table.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:39:### Step 4 - Test the promoted observable on the full stretching mechanism
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:41:This is the right battleground. If the observable does not hit the full stretching mechanism, the route is mostly dead. But the step still grants too much discretion by allowing the chain to `freeze one stretching representation`. Different representations expose or hide different debts. If the branch gets to choose the friendliest representation after Step 3, it can manufacture a misleading sense of contact with the mechanism.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:43:The requirement to distinguish `near-field gain` from `exterior or nonlocal remainder` is correct, but the step badly underestimates how often the exterior remainder is the actual problem. For Biot-Savart-driven stretching, the hard issue is frequently that local alignment buys something only after one has already controlled a nonlocal tail or global geometry. This step identifies the issue without forcing a realistic strategy for paying it.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:45:The `declared burden share of the full stretching term` is too vague. A route can declare a burden share of 5 percent and still be irrelevant. The chain should require either a quantitatively meaningful fraction or a precise explanation of why controlling that share propagates to the endpoint. Without that, Step 4 can be passed by a small local depletion story that never threatens the decisive remainder.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:49:### Step 5 - Bridge to criterion scale or contradiction scale with a hard artifact
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:53:Benchmarking against the `neutral-Eulerian comparator` and `closest Constantin-Fefferman-type prior art` is necessary, but the order is wrong. Prior-art comparison should have been present in Step 1, not introduced only after a preferred geometry package and observable have already been selected. Otherwise the chain is structurally biased toward rediscovering known direction-regularity logic with nicer packaging.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:57:The kill condition is one of the better ones in the document, because prior-art collapse is the central danger here. But by Step 5, the chain has already spent too long on internal package discipline before checking whether it is just recreating classical geometric depletion themes under new labels.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:65:The failure taxonomy is decent, but incomplete. It omits endpoint mismatch, criterion-currency mismatch, and prior-art equivalence that is not literal collapse but still leaves no real novelty. Those are not edge cases; they are among the most likely failure modes for this exact geometry route.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:75:Third, the prior-art overlap risk is extreme. `Direction coherence`, `local Beltrami deficit`, `tube persistence`, and a bridge to `Constantin-Fefferman-type criterion` are already living inside a mature geometric-depletion neighborhood. If the novelty is just an adapted package that tracks geometry more sympathetically, the route is probably re-encoding the old insight that aligned vorticity weakens stretching, while inheriting the same old blockage: maintaining and exploiting that alignment at the right scale without paying prohibitive derivative or localization debt.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:77:Fourth, the chain hides a major assumption that never gets justified: that the chosen geometric observable can be both persistent enough to track and strong enough to affect the full stretching or criterion ledger. Usually one gets one of those at the expense of the other. Cheap observables are too weak; strong observables require derivative control, axis selection, curvature bounds, or threshold stability that are already close to the core difficulty.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:81:Sixth, the chain is less distinct from the transport branch than it claims. A tube-following or high-vorticity tracking package is already importing quasi-Lagrangian structure, just under geometric branding. So the asserted separation from `deterministic transport clocks` is not clean. The route may be borrowing transport machinery while denying that dependence at the branding layer.
../../planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:85:The chain does have real strengths. It is unusually honest about localization debt, and Step 4 correctly insists that local depletion stories do not matter unless they touch the full stretching mechanism. As an obstruction generator, this chain could be useful.
