../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The selected chain has two real strengths: it is unusually honest about localization debt, and it correctly identifies full stretching contact as the decisive battleground. But it still gives geometry too much procedural sympathy. Too much of Steps 1 through 4 can be completed with package selection, observable screening, and narrative accounting before the branch is forced to write down a serious theorem-facing proposition.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-01.md:7:The correct repair is not to discard the branch. It is to recast it as a criterion-first, falsification-first geometry stress test. Geometry should be treated as a hypothesis under audit, not as the default "most mission-facing" mechanism.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-01.md:17:### 2. Step 1 allows cosmetic package discipline and uses the wrong comparator
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-01.md:21:The attacker is right that naming the killed neutral-Eulerian package is not enough. The decisive comparator must be the closest live geometric prior art, not just a discarded straw package. The original Step 1 also allowed too much slack by permitting heterogeneous "advantages" such as persistence, criterion compatibility, or full-stretching control without fixing which one is actually being claimed.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-01.md:23:The refined chain should require an endpoint-facing candidate proposition and a prior-art comparator before package optimism is allowed to accumulate.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-01.md:41:The selected chain was correct to ask whether the observable touches the full stretching mechanism rather than a descriptive fragment. The attacker is still right that allowing one friendly stretching representation and an unspecified "burden share" leaves too much room for false positives. The refined chain should either use a canonical representation plus a translation check, or require representation-robust conclusions. It should also demand a quantitatively meaningful share or an explicit propagation-to-endpoint explanation.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-01.md:59:This is the right global reading. The original chain assumed geometry remained the leading mechanism before it had been re-earned under stricter standards. The prior-art overlap risk is severe, especially around direction coherence, Beltrami deficit, tube persistence, and criterion interfaces. The branch is much more likely to yield a presentable obstruction memo than a genuinely new positive route. That is acceptable, but it should be stated explicitly.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-01.md:65:The attacker identifies a real contamination risk. Tube-following or high-vorticity tracking packages can import transport structure under geometric branding. But that does not erase the branch distinction entirely. It means the refined chain should explicitly test whether any apparent gain is genuinely geometric or is actually a transport-dependent hybrid.
