../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-02.md:7:The attacker is mostly correct. The original chain has good hygiene instincts: it freezes one observable, one endpoint, and asks for a hard artifact. But the critique correctly identifies that the decisive risk is earlier and harsher than the chain admits: theorem-floor admissibility, proxy-bridge inflation, localization/interface mismatch, and prior-art redundancy all need to become gating conditions, not later bookkeeping.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-02.md:13:### 1. Step 1 is too permissive about observable choice and proxy fallback
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-02.md:17:The critique is right that the original menu mixes genuinely different object classes, and that "named bridge burden" is too weak. A proxy class is acceptable only if the bridge back to suitable-weak / LEI data is explicitly quantified and clearly cheaper than the target theorem. That stricter admissibility test belongs at Step 1.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-02.md:35:The critique is right that the route matters only if the promoted quantity enters an actual LEI / CKN line in the right scale and units. The refined chain should treat insertion as a full gain-versus-debt interface test, with explicit rejection of cross-currency gains lacking a transfer lemma.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-02.md:47:The warning is fair: for this branch the "missing lemma" can easily be the whole theorem in disguise. The refined chain should add proxy-bridge inflation and prior-art redundancy to the failure taxonomy and should downgrade aggressively when the remaining lemma is not genuinely narrower. I do not accept that a narrow conditional remainder is impossible in principle, only that the original chain did not guard against fake narrowness tightly enough.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-02.md:59:This is the main substantive criticism. Admissibility on suitable-weak / LEI data, or a quantitatively cheaper proxy descent, is not setup debt. It governs the whole branch and should be fused with endpoint-interface screening near the front of the chain.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-02.md:65:The critique is right. A transport-stretching branch can easily rename known strain criteria, deformation heuristics, or coarse-grained observables without changing the burden ledger. The refined chain should require a prior-art comparator and a concrete claimed delta before continuing.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-02.md:71:This follows from the earlier points. Earlier hard stops are needed for proxy inflation, defect-ledger non-separation, and endpoint-currency mismatch.
../../planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-02.md:83:- require direct theorem-floor definability or a proxy bridge demonstrably cheaper than the target theorem;
